This paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms and optimization techniques to improve search and discovery in complex domains. Specifically, it proposes a new approach called behavior domination that combines novelty search with multiobjective optimization. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the focus on optimization and search algorithms, cs.AI and cs.NE are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.SE, and cs.SY.
